$tmx['hp_export_data']='With this form you can export RackMap data in several formats. The "exclude" field allows you to remove some fields from the output. You can use the following keywords to exclude fields from the output of the report. Use these keywords in a space separated list in the exclude field of the form: * user: removes any reference to any field containing the word user, for example an ILO username; * password: removes any reference to a field containing the word password, an example is the iLO password.; * license: removes any reference to any field containing the word license, for instance a software license or ILO upgrade license; * child: removes any reference to an object that is part of larger device or parent, for example hard drive, PSU, processor, RAM module etc; * connection: removes the connection section for example power, virtual or network connections between objects; * permissions: Removes all permission tables relating to objects; * object: removes any detailed information about every child and parent object - only the reports such as rack view and capacity will be displayed; * capacity: this removes the capacity report from the export. ** Note: You can add any other field in the system to exclude, however the above are the main fields recommended for use.';
